text:
Expenditure on national security and defense in the budget 2020 is 5.45% of GDP, - Ministry of Finance

05 Nov 2019, 16:27


In the draft law on the state budget 2020, expenditures on national security and defense make up UAH 245.8 billion or 5.45% of GDP.

This was reported by the press service of the Ministry of Finance of Ukraine.
In particular, the general fund's expenditure on this function is planned to be directed to:

cash and wages (with accruals) - UAH 141.4 billion (+ UAH 14.4 billion by 2019);
medicines and dressings - UAH 657.8 million (+ UAH 82.8 million by 2019);
food - UAH 4.84 billion (+ UAH 248.1 million by 2019);
payment for utilities and energy - UAH 4.9 billion (+ UAH 510.7 million by 2019);
creation, procurement, modernization and repair of weapons and military (special) equipment - UAH 35.4 billion (+ UAH 7.8 billion by 2019);
payment of lump sum cash benefits in case of death (death), disability or partial disability and other social benefits - UAH 6.66 billion (+ UAH 2.44 billion by 2019);
housing construction (purchase) - UAH 2.23 billion (UAH +389.8 million by 2019).

It should be reminded that on November 3, government officials met for an extraordinary meeting, during which, among other things, they approved the draft budget 2020 before the second reading.
Oleksiy Honcharuk said that in the budget for 2020 the government does not seek additional resources in raising taxes, but proposes to reduce administrative costs and to serve the government and central executive bodies by an average of 10%.
Goncharuk also called new figures for the state budget for 2020.

